                     <binding notBefore="1500" notAfter="1700">
                        <p>The binding in 1655 was velvet, and the title on a label, metal bosses,
         clasps, clasp-fittings and corner pieces were re-imposed on a leather binding made in the
         second half of the 17th century. The bosses have now disappeared. (For a list of manuscripts with comparable bindings, see <ref target="https://medieval.bodleian.ox.ac.uk/catalog/manuscript_1275">MS. Bodl. 218</ref>)</p>
